==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[exactus]]''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-exact.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''exact'''
#Precisely agreeing with a [[standard]], a [[fact]], or the [[truth]]; perfectly [[conforming]]; neither [[exceeding]] nor [[falling]] [[short]] in any respect; [[true]]; [[correct]]; [[precise]].
#:''The clock keeps '''exact''' time.''
#:''He paid the '''exact''' debt.''
#:''an '''exact''' copy of a letter''
#:'''''exact''' accounts''
#Habitually [[careful]] to agree with a standard, a [[rule]], or a [[promise]]; accurate; [[methodical]]; [[punctual]]
#:''a man '''exact''' in observing an appointment''
#:''In my doings I was '''exact'''.''
#Precisely or definitely conceived or stated; [[strict]].

====Derived terms====
*[[exactly]]
*[[exactness]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[tarkka]] (1-3), [[eksakti]] (1,3), [[täsmällinen]] (1-3)

===Verb===
'''exact'''
#''(transitive)'' Demand and [[enforce]] the [[payment]] or [[performance]] of.
#''(transitive)'' Make [[desirable]] or necessary.
#''(transitive)'' [[Extract]] forcibly.
#:''to '''exact''' revenge''

